<li id="cite_note-48"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48" title="">^</a></b> Decety, J., Michalska, K.J., Akitsuki, Y., &amp; Lahey, B. (2008). Atypical empathic responses in adolescents with aggressive conduct disorder: a functional MRI investigation. Biological Psychology, Epub ahead of print.</li>
<li id="cite_note-49"><b><a href="#cite_ref-49" title="">^</a></b> This is cited by Phoebe Caldwell, an author on ASD, who writes: <i>What is clear is that, while people on the spectrum may not respond easily to external gestures/sounds, they do respond most readily if the initiative they witness is already part of their repertoire. This points to the selective use of incoming information rather than absence of recognition. It would appear that people with autism are actually rather good at recognition and imitation if the action they perceive is one that has meaning and significance for their brains. As regards the failure of empathetic response, it would appear that at least some people with autism are oversensitive to the feelings of others rather than immune to them, but cannot handle the painful feed-back that this initiates in the body, and have therefore learnt to suppress this facility.</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-50"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50" title="">^</a></b> Beaumont, R. and Newcombe, P. (2006) Theory of mind and central coherence in adults with high-functioning autism or Asperger syndrome, Autism: The International Journal of Research &amp; Practice 10.(4) 365-382</li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51" title="">^</a></b> Hill, E., Berthoz, S., &amp; Frith, U (2004) 'Brief report: cognitive processing of own emotions in individuals with autistic spectrum disorder and in their relatives.' Journal of Autism and Developmental Disorders 34, (2) 229-235.</li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52" title="">^</a></b> Taylor, G.J. and Bagby, R.M &amp; Parker, J.D.A. Disorders of Affect Regulation: Alexithymia in Medical and Psychiatric Illness. (1997) Cambridge Uni. Press.</li>
<li id="cite_note-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53" title="">^</a></b> Rogers K, Dziobek I, Hassenstab J, Wolf OT, Convit A. Who cares? Revisiting empathy in Asperger syndrome. J Autism Dev Disord. 2007 Apr;37(4):709-15.</li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54" title="">^</a></b> Dapretto, M., Davies, M.S., Pfeifer, J.H., Scott, A.A., Sigman, M., Bookheimer, S.Y., &amp; Iacoboni, M. (2006). Understanding emotions in others: mirror neuron dysfunction in children with autism spectrum disorders. Nature Neuroscience, 9, 28-31.</li>
<li id="cite_note-55"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55" title="">^</a></b> Bastiaanen, J., Thioux, M., &amp; Keysers (2008). Mirror-neuron system not broken in adults with ASD for viewing emotions of others. Fifteen Cognitive Neuroscience Society Meeting, San Francisco, April.</li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56" title="">^</a></b> Wyschogrod, E. 1981. Empathy and sympathy as tactile encounter. J Med Philos 6 (1):25-43</li>
<li id="cite_note-57"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFAronsonWilson_Timothy_D..2C_and_Akert.2C_Robin2007"><a href="/wiki/Elliot_Aronson" title="Elliot Aronson">Aronson, Elliot</a>; Wilson Timothy D., and Akert, Robin (2007). <i>Social Psychology, 6th Edition</i>. <a href="/wiki/Prentice_Hall" title="Prentice Hall">Prentice Hall</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0132382458" class="internal">ISBN 0132382458</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Social+Psychology%2C+6th+Edition&amp;rft.aulast=Aronson&amp;rft.aufirst=Elliot&amp;rft.au=Aronson%2C+Elliot&amp;rft.au=Wilson+Timothy+D.%2C+and+Akert%2C+Robin&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPrentice+Hall%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0132382458&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Empathy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-58"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFDale_J._Langford.2C_Sara_E._Crager.2C_Zarrar_Shehzad.2C_Shad_B._Smith.2C_Susana_G._Sotocinal.2C_Jeremy_S._Levenstadt.2C_Mona_Lisa_Chanda.2C_.5B.5BDaniel_Levitin.7CDaniel_J._Levitin.5D.5D.2C_Jeffrey_S._Mogil2006">Dale J. Langford, Sara E. Crager, Zarrar Shehzad, Shad B. Smith, Susana G. Sotocinal, Jeremy S. Levenstadt, Mona Lisa Chanda, <a href="/wiki/Daniel_Levitin" title="Daniel Levitin">Daniel J. Levitin</a>, Jeffrey S. Mogil (June 30, 2006). "Social Modulation of Pain as Evidence for Empathy in Mice". <i>Science</i> <b>312</b>: 1967–1970. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1126%2Fscience.1128322" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1126%2Fscience.1128322" rel="nofollow">10.1126/science.1128322</a></span>. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16809545" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16809545">PMID 16809545</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Social+Modulation+of+Pain+as+Evidence+for+Empathy+in+Mice&amp;rft.jtitle=Science&amp;rft.aulast=Dale+J.+Langford%2C+Sara+E.+Crager%2C+Zarrar+Shehzad%2C+Shad+B.+Smith%2C+Susana+G.+Sotocinal%2C+Jeremy+S.+Levenstadt%2C+Mona+Lisa+Chanda%2C+%5B%5BDaniel+Levitin%7CDaniel+J.+Levitin%5D%5D%2C+Jeffrey+S.+Mogil&amp;rft.au=Dale+J.+Langford%2C+Sara+E.+Crager%2C+Zarrar+Shehzad%2C+Shad+B.+Smith%2C+Susana+G.+Sotocinal%2C+Jeremy+S.+Levenstadt%2C+Mona+Lisa+Chanda%2C+%5B%5BDaniel+Levitin%7CDaniel+J.+Levitin%5D%5D%2C+Jeffrey+S.+Mogil&amp;rft.date=June+30%2C+2006&amp;rft.volume=312&amp;rft.pages=1967%E2%80%931970&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1126%2Fscience.1128322&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/16809545&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Empathy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-59"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59" title="">^</a></b> Gauss, Charles Edward. 1973. Empathy. In Dictionary of the history of ideas: Studies of selected pivotal ideas, edited by P. P. Wiener. New York: Scribner. 85-89.</li>
<li id="cite_note-60"><b><a href="#cite_ref-60" title="">^</a></b> Jenkins, K. (1991) <i>Re-thinking History</i> London: Routledge</li>
<li id="cite_note-61"><b><a href="#cite_ref-61" title="">^</a></b> Pozzi, G. (1976) <i>Prefazione 6.L'elemento storico e politico -sociale, in G.B. Marino, L'Adone</i> Milano</li>
